The paper focuses on self-supervised learning for object picking, which is a common task in robotics (cs.RO). The method involves using deep neural networks for object detection (cs.CV), similarity evaluation (cs.LG), and feedback control (cs.AI). The proposed approach also incorporates metric learning to determine the optimal grasping position (cs.SY).
